Framework-agnostic priority order for element selection in Playwright.

## Priority

```
1. data-testid                     ← primary, ESLint-enforced on interactive elements
2. getByRole('role', { name })     ← accessibility-first fallback
3. getByText('exact text')         ← content-stable elements only
4. CSS selector                    ← last resort; requires inline comment explaining why
```

Higher = preferred. Reach lower only when the higher option genuinely cannot satisfy the test.

## Page-object-only rule

All locators live inside page objects. Inline locators in step definitions or specs are a Pass 1 CRITICAL violation.

```ts
// ✅ correct
class ClaimsPage {
  readonly submitClaimButton = this.page.getByTestId('submit-claim-button');
  async submit() { await this.submitClaimButton.click(); }
}
// In spec:
await claimsPage.submit();

// ❌ wrong
test('submits', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.getByTestId('submit-claim-button').click(); // Pass 1 CRITICAL violation
});
```

## `data-testid` naming

Format: `<feature>-<element>-<action>` — kebab-case.

| Example                         | Why it works                                        |
| ------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------- |
| `submit-claim-button`           | feature=submit-claim, element=button, action=submit |
| `claims-list-row`               | collection — container + row pattern                |
| `login-email-input`             | clear feature + element + type                      |

Reject: `submit-btn` (abbreviated), `button-1` (ordinal), `SubmitClaimButton` (PascalCase), `data-test` / `data-cy` / `data-qa` / `data-pgr-id` (use `data-testid`).

## CSS escape hatch

CSS selectors require an inline comment citing one of:

- `third-party widget; no attr hook available`
- `shadow-DOM boundary; data-testid not observable from light DOM`
- `legacy component; scheduled for refactor in <ticket-ref>`
- `framework injects class we cannot override`

```ts
readonly datePicker = this.page.locator('.mui-datepicker-input'); // third-party widget; no attr hook available
```

## Do-not-use list

Never acceptable in page objects:

| Pattern                                | Why                                   |
| -------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| `nth-child`, `nth-of-type`, `eq(n)`    | Breaks on sibling reorder             |
| XPath (`//button[...]`)                | Brittle, unreadable                   |
| Utility-class selectors (`.btn`)       | Styling changes on theme updates      |
| Generated IDs (`#__next-route-0_123`)  | Hash regenerates on build             |
| `waitForTimeout(ms)`                   | Non-deterministic — use `waitFor*`    |

Any of these triggers a Pass 1 CRITICAL review failure.

## Framework attribute syntax

| Framework | Attribute form                                          |
| --------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| React/JSX | `<button data-testid="submit-claim-button">`            |
| Vue       | `<button :data-testid="'submit-claim-button'">`         |
| Svelte    | `<button data-testid="submit-claim-button">`            |
| Angular   | `<button [attr.data-testid]="'submit-claim-button'">`   |
| Solid     | `<button data-testid="submit-claim-button">`            |
